01:02.028 --> 01:03.928
[ Tires Screeching ]

01:05.298 --> 01:07.232
D'oh!
[ Screams ]

01:11.037 --> 01:12.937
[ All ]
Whoa!

01:24.851 --> 01:27.911
## [ Singing ]

01:28.021 --> 01:31.081
## [ Continues ]

01:37.464 --> 01:41.093
## [ Singing Rock Song ]

01:44.304 --> 01:48.172
I didn't think it was physically possible,
but this both sucks and blows.

01:51.044 --> 01:54.241
## [ Singing Ends ]

01:57.450 --> 02:00.613
[ Chuckles ]
Whew. Mercy.

02:00.720 --> 02:04.554
Good evening. Our old friend Noah Webster
defines ''laughter''...

02:04.657 --> 02:07.717
as ''the act or sound of laughing.''

02:07.827 --> 02:09.294
<i>[ Nelson ]
Ha-ha.!</i>

02:09.395 --> 02:11.625
[ Chuckles ]
Well illustrated, Nelson.

02:11.731 --> 02:15.223
And now, fasten your funny bones
for Groundskeeper-

02:15.335 --> 02:18.065
Oh. Or should I say
''Grinskeeper''?

02:18.171 --> 02:21.038
No, I'm sorry.
Groundskeeper was correct. Willie!

02:21.141 --> 02:24.235
<i>- ## [ Bagpipes ]
- [ Applause ]</i>

02:24.344 --> 02:27.108
How many of you hail from
the fair city of Edinburgh?

02:29.182 --> 02:31.082
So, have you noticed...

02:31.184 --> 02:34.585
how North Edinburgh golfers
putt like this...

02:34.687 --> 02:38.623
and South Edinburgh golfers
putt like this?

02:39.692 --> 02:42.217
<i>- [ Man Coughs ]
- Eh?</i>

02:42.328 --> 02:44.262
- ## [ Bagpipes ]
- Eh?

02:44.364 --> 02:47.595
<i>- [ Crickets Chirping ]
- Oh, I see.</i>

02:47.700 --> 02:50.260
Willie's not funny unless
he's down on his knees...

02:50.370 --> 02:52.930
scooping up your little brats' puke!

02:53.039 --> 02:55.200
[ Laughing, Applauding ]

02:55.308 --> 02:57.208
Thank you! You've been great!

02:57.310 --> 02:59.107
<i>##[Jazz ]</i>

02:59.212 --> 03:01.112
## [ Singing ]

03:02.515 --> 03:06.349
## [ Continues ]

03:06.452 --> 03:08.750
- [ Groaning ]
- ## [ Continues ]

03:08.855 --> 03:11.050
<i>- [ Balloons Popping ]
- Kill me.</i>

03:11.157 --> 03:14.217
Well, Seymour,
it seems we put together...

03:14.327 --> 03:16.522
a baseball team,
and I was wondering-

03:16.629 --> 03:18.529
Who's on first?

03:18.631 --> 03:21.395
Yes. Not the pronoun,
but rather a player...

03:21.501 --> 03:24.061
with the unlikely name
of Who is on first.

03:24.170 --> 03:26.070
Yes. Well, that's
just great, Seymour.

03:26.172 --> 03:29.471
We've been out here six seconds.
You've already managed to blow the routine.

03:29.576 --> 03:31.567
Sexless freak.

03:31.678 --> 03:35.409
<i>- ##[ Rim Shot ]
- [ Laughs ]</i>

03:35.515 --> 03:38.245
Well, seems as though
we're just about at the halfway point...

03:38.351 --> 03:40.979
- so why don't we call it intermission?
- [ Chattering ]

03:41.087 --> 03:42.987
Whoa! Don't go too far.

03:43.089 --> 03:46.820
If you like cafeteria workers
in Beatle wigs with tennis racket guitars...

03:46.926 --> 03:48.860
you won't want to miss
the second half.

03:48.962 --> 03:51.055
- Oh, no! No!
- [ All Shouting ]

03:53.199 --> 03:55.190
You drive. I eat.

03:55.301 --> 03:58.099
Dad, you were supposed
to pay for those snacks.

03:58.204 --> 04:00.604
I saw Krabappel's butt.
I paid.

04:02.108 --> 04:03.803
[ Horns Honking ]

04:03.910 --> 04:06.538
Whoopsie.
Mm, this could take a minute.

04:06.646 --> 04:08.876
- There's an opening, Mom.
- I don't know.

04:08.982 --> 04:12.110
I- I hate to change lanes
once I get going.

04:12.218 --> 04:15.187
- That's really for race car drivers.
- Mom, to your left.

04:15.288 --> 04:16.812
He's letting you in. Go!

04:16.923 --> 04:19.447
<i>- [ Lisa ] Come on, Mom.!
- [ Homer ] Gun it, woman.!</i>

04:19.559 --> 04:22.858
No. No. As soon as I get over,
that lane will stop moving.

04:22.962 --> 04:25.931
Erma Bombeck said so,
and Dave Barry agrees.

04:28.001 --> 04:31.129
<i>- [ Horns Honking ]
- Aw! You suck, Marge.</i>

04:32.338 --> 04:34.806
- Come on! Move it, you clowns!
- [ Honking ]

04:34.907 --> 04:37.102
What in blazes?

04:42.548 --> 04:44.743
So long, schlubs!

04:44.851 --> 04:47.251
Wow. Did you see that thing, Marge?

04:47.353 --> 04:49.287
So powerful. So commanding.

04:49.389 --> 04:52.256
<i>- So forceful and raw.
- [ Horse Neighs ]</i>

04:52.358 --> 04:55.054
It didn't ask. It just took.

04:55.228 --> 04:58.595
<i>- ##[ Man Singing Country Music ]
- [ Man #2 Shouts ]</i>

05:00.700 --> 05:05.034
<i>- ##[ Ends ]
- [ Groaning ]</i>

05:05.138 --> 05:07.538
Oh, Canyonero.

05:07.640 --> 05:09.574
[ Laughs ]
Go ahead. Drool all you want.

05:09.676 --> 05:13.806
You can't hurt that finish.
Now, rainwater- that'll strip it right off.

05:13.913 --> 05:16.848
Ah, I shouldn't have
said that. I'm Gil.

05:16.949 --> 05:18.849
Hey, a red one!

05:18.951 --> 05:21.112
<i>[ Laughing ]</i>

05:21.220 --> 05:23.347
Can I buy that? Please?

05:23.456 --> 05:26.050
Well, you- If you-
[ Babbles ] Really?

05:26.159 --> 05:29.754
Wha- Ha!
Hot dog! A sale!

05:29.862 --> 05:32.057
[ Laughing ]

05:32.165 --> 05:34.395
- [ Laughing Continues ] Huh?
- I'll take it from here, Gil.

05:34.500 --> 05:37.128
No! Wait! Ah, no!
You can't take my sale!

05:37.236 --> 05:40.069
My wife's gonna leave me
if I don't start bringing in the green.

05:40.173 --> 05:43.074
Come on. Let me have this one, Stan.
I'm begging you.

05:43.176 --> 05:46.043
Look at me.
I'm begging you, Stan.

05:46.145 --> 05:49.012
Mm-hmm.
Let's go write this up, shall we?

05:52.018 --> 05:54.816
Honey, you should've seen me
with my last customer. I-

05:54.921 --> 05:58.857
No, but I came so close.
This guy was-

05:58.958 --> 06:02.018
Whose voice is that?
Is that Fred?

06:02.128 --> 06:05.495
Ah, you said it was over!
No, don't put him on!

06:05.598 --> 06:07.896
Hello, Fred. H-Hi.

06:09.268 --> 06:11.168
Okay. You've got
the undercoating...

06:11.270 --> 06:13.568
clear coating, rustproofing,
under guard spray...

06:13.673 --> 06:16.301
<i>Gravel Guard XJ,
Vita-Seal, Repels-It...</i>

06:16.409 --> 06:20.607
but if you want to protect the paint,
you better keep it in this tent.

06:20.713 --> 06:23.375
- Will do.
- Okay. Here's how your lease breaks down:

06:23.483 --> 06:28.511
This is your down payment, then here's
your monthly, and there's your weekly.

06:28.621 --> 06:30.816
- And that's it, right?
- Yup.

06:30.923 --> 06:33.551
Oh, then after your final monthly payment,
there's the routine C.B.P....

06:33.659 --> 06:36.423
- or crippling balloon payment.
- But that's not for a while, right?

06:36.529 --> 06:39.726
- Right.
- Sweet.

06:39.832 --> 06:41.356
<i>[ Bird Caws ]</i>

06:41.467 --> 06:42.991
- Whoo! Hello!
- Whoo!

06:43.102 --> 06:44.569
Hey, baby!

06:46.606 --> 06:50.906
Oh. Sorry, Homer. We thought you were
one of those hot-to-trot soccer moms.

06:51.010 --> 06:53.672
Yeah. You don't see many men
driving the ''F'' Series.

06:53.780 --> 06:55.680
Huh?

06:55.782 --> 06:59.445
See? Instead of a cigarette lighter,
it's got a lipstick holder.

06:59.552 --> 07:01.315
[ Gasps ]

07:01.421 --> 07:05.414
Ah, crap! It's a girl's car!
I can't drive this!

07:05.525 --> 07:08.790
Oh, sure, you can, doll face.
[ Kisses ]

07:08.895 --> 07:12.194
[ Chuckles ] Pretty thing like you
can do whatever she wants.

07:12.298 --> 07:14.266
[ Both Laughing ]

07:14.367 --> 07:16.631
Shut up! Screw you guys!

07:16.736 --> 07:18.931
[ Both Laughing ]

07:19.038 --> 07:22.735
<i>Lousy ''F''Series frilly, girlie, fruity car.
[ Mutters ]</i>

07:22.842 --> 07:25.333
Where's your keys?
I'm taking your car to work.

07:25.445 --> 07:29.609
You cashed in your 401 (k) to buy
that stupid Canyonero.

07:29.715 --> 07:32.843
- Why can't you drive it?
- Are you saying I'm gay?

07:32.952 --> 07:35.978
Because if that's what you think,
then just come right out and say it.

07:36.088 --> 07:39.455
I don't think you're gay.
I just have to do my grocery shopping.

07:39.559 --> 07:41.459
Now, please, give me my keys.

07:41.561 --> 07:43.461
Fine.

07:43.563 --> 07:46.623
## [ Humming ]

07:46.732 --> 07:48.893
- [ Engine Starts ]
- [ Laughs ]

07:49.001 --> 07:51.367
- Ha-ha! Sucker!
- Oh!

07:54.340 --> 07:57.309
Good Lord!
[ Groans ]

07:57.410 --> 07:59.935
How am I supposed
to get in this beast?

08:02.448 --> 08:05.975
Hmm. Well, that's a nice feature.

08:07.086 --> 08:10.487
Not much headroom though.
Ooh!

08:10.590 --> 08:14.185
Oh, I guess I can
drive it for a little while.

08:14.293 --> 08:16.523
But, Mom, I read that
sport utility vehicles...

08:16.629 --> 08:19.189
are more likely to be involved
in fatal accidents.

08:19.298 --> 08:21.596
Fatal to the people in the other car.
Let's roll.

08:21.701 --> 08:25.467
Hang on. The manual says
I need to log on to the onboard computer.

08:25.571 --> 08:28.369
M-A-R-G-E.

08:28.474 --> 08:31.568
[ Electronic Female Voice ] Hello, Marge.
Where would you like to go today?

08:31.677 --> 08:35.841
[ Gasps ] No one has ever asked me
that before in my life.

08:38.251 --> 08:40.947
Well, that's a first.
I've never been able...

08:41.053 --> 08:44.386
to fit 3 2 grocery bags
into one car before.

08:44.490 --> 08:48.153
Ew! Why is Courtney Love
on the Wheaties box?

08:48.261 --> 08:52.061
- Hmm. I thought it was Sandy Duncan.
- Uh-oh. Gridlock at 1 2:00.

08:52.164 --> 08:54.792
- [ Horns Honking ]
- [ People Shouting ]

08:58.271 --> 09:02.207
Oh, crud.
And we're so close to the house.

09:02.308 --> 09:06.335
Um, I don't want to alarm you,
but the ice cream's starting to go south.

09:08.614 --> 09:11.674
Hmm. Mm-hmm.
[ Gags ]

09:11.784 --> 09:14.184
Hey, give me some of that!
[ Screams ]

09:14.287 --> 09:17.120
Mom! Bart sprayed
whipped cream in my eye!

09:17.223 --> 09:19.350
- I did not.
- [ Screams ]

09:19.458 --> 09:23.292
- [ Both Grunting ]
- Kids, cut it out!

09:23.396 --> 09:26.923
- [ Sighs ] All right.
- Hey!

09:27.033 --> 09:29.524
Come on, Mom.
Just cut across the field.

09:29.635 --> 09:32.365
Oh, I don't know.
It doesn't seem right.

09:32.471 --> 09:34.996
[ Scoffs ] Do you want to spend
your whole life doing what's right?

09:35.107 --> 09:37.007
Of course not.

09:39.745 --> 09:42.873
<i>- Let's do it!
- ##[ Man Singing Country Music ]</i>

09:42.982 --> 09:45.212
<i>[ Man #2 Shouts ]</i>

09:45.318 --> 09:47.752
<i>- ##[ Continues ]
- Whoa! You the man, Mom!</i>

09:47.853 --> 09:49.753
Out of my way, nature!

09:49.855 --> 09:52.221
[ Chittering ]

09:52.325 --> 09:54.816
<i>##[ Ends ]</i>

10:00.333 --> 10:02.563
[ Gasps ]

10:02.668 --> 10:05.398
Look at me, Lise.
I'm Baron Von Chicken Pants.

10:05.504 --> 10:07.972
[ Clucking ]

10:08.074 --> 10:10.099
Bart, that's
tomorrow night's dinner.

10:10.209 --> 10:12.734
- You're tomorrow night's dinner.
- Mom!

10:12.845 --> 10:15.905
Bart took what I said
and turned it into an insult!

10:16.015 --> 10:17.676
That's nice, dear!

10:17.783 --> 10:20.616
Okay, Mr. Peanut,
you think you can keep-

10:22.021 --> 10:24.581
[ Sputtering ]

10:24.690 --> 10:26.920
A three-chambered peanut!

10:27.026 --> 10:30.587
Marge, look what I did!
Come quick! Hurry!

10:30.696 --> 10:32.891
Marge?

10:32.999 --> 10:35.263
Marge?

10:35.368 --> 10:38.269
- Marge, you've been out there all morning.
- So?

10:38.371 --> 10:42.569
So, lying on the couch and eating stuff
isn't the same if you aren't around to see it.

10:42.675 --> 10:45.269
Oh, I'll come watch you
do nothing after I try out...

10:45.378 --> 10:48.142
my new high-intensity
halogen headlights.

10:51.283 --> 10:55.652
[ Laughs ]
Nobody will ever cut me off again.

10:55.755 --> 10:57.689
Ah, please come in!

10:57.790 --> 11:02.955
Maggie smells bad, and the cat wants
something, but I don't know what.

11:03.062 --> 11:07.021
I'm almost done.
And tell Bart to get out of my purse.

11:09.001 --> 11:11.629
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

11:16.409 --> 11:18.343
<i>- [ Marge ] S.U. V. coming through.
- [ Horn Honking ]</i>

11:18.444 --> 11:21.311
<i>- Open up for Marge. Thank you.
- [ Honking Continues ]</i>

11:21.414 --> 11:23.405
<i>Thank- Whoa.!</i>

11:23.516 --> 11:26.280
<i>And daylight.!
Come on.! Come on.!</i>

11:26.385 --> 11:29.752
- [ Honking Continues ]
- Geez. Try the gas pedal, Grandma.

11:29.855 --> 11:32.016
It's right there next to the brake.

11:32.124 --> 11:35.992
- Oh, for God's s- Go back to New Jersey.
- [ Horn Honks ]

11:36.095 --> 11:38.290
[ Tires Squeal, Screech ]

11:40.366 --> 11:42.926
[ Muttering ]

11:43.035 --> 11:44.502
- [ Muffled Shout ]
- [ Honks ]

11:44.603 --> 11:47.731
Come on, come on!
Get that corpse off the road!

11:47.840 --> 11:50.001
The streets are for the living!

11:50.109 --> 11:53.442
- [ Both ] Whoa!
- Slow down, you maniac!

11:53.546 --> 11:55.946
Show some respect for this
coffin full of bricks...

11:56.048 --> 11:58.846
representing
a young man lost at sea.

12:00.086 --> 12:03.021
- Hey!
- [ Siren Wailing ]

12:04.323 --> 12:06.655
Oh, great. What did I do?

12:09.261 --> 12:12.992
- This better be important.
- Can the sweet talk, Thelma & Louise.

12:13.099 --> 12:15.158
You have a serious mental illness.

12:15.267 --> 12:18.065
The technical term is ''road rage.''

12:18.170 --> 12:21.071
I'll see you tomorrow morning
at traffic school, speedy.

12:21.173 --> 12:23.903
And you got exactly five seconds
to get out of my sight.

12:24.009 --> 12:26.739
- [ Grumbles ]
- [ Tires Squeal ]

12:26.846 --> 12:29.974
[ Sighs ]
Why are the pretty ones always insane?

12:31.383 --> 12:33.749
[ Marge Groaning ]

12:35.187 --> 12:38.748
Okay. I assume you all know
why you're here.

12:38.858 --> 12:40.883
That's right.
You're all angry...

12:40.993 --> 12:42.858
<i>- sick people.
- [ Snoring ]</i>

12:42.962 --> 12:48.093
But over these next eight hours, you will be
broken down to the level of infants...

12:48.200 --> 12:51.328
then rebuilt as functional
members of society...

12:51.437 --> 12:54.429
then broken down again,
then lunch...

12:54.540 --> 12:56.770
then, if there's time,
rebuilt once more.

12:56.876 --> 12:58.776
All right, roll it, Lou.

13:00.179 --> 13:02.739
## [ Instrumental ]

13:02.848 --> 13:04.873
Hello. I'm Sergeant Crew...

13:04.984 --> 13:07.384
and I'm here
to talk to you about...

13:07.486 --> 13:10.944
road... rage.

13:11.056 --> 13:14.355
- Duh!
- Quiet, fatso! The sergeant's talking!

13:14.460 --> 13:15.927
Go on, dear.

13:16.028 --> 13:18.895
In these modern,
hectic days of fast food...

13:18.998 --> 13:23.560
answering machines and one-night stands,
people are getting angrier.

13:23.669 --> 13:26.297
Now, what you're about
to see is not pretty.

13:28.841 --> 13:33.278
Cut me off, will you?
[ Grunting ]

13:33.379 --> 13:36.473
<i>- [ Horn Honking ]
- Learn to drive, dimwit!</i>

13:37.616 --> 13:40.380
I sentence you to kiss my ass.

13:40.486 --> 13:42.681
[ Screaming ]

13:42.788 --> 13:45.188
Look familiar? It should.

13:45.291 --> 13:47.486
Anger is what
makes America great.

13:47.593 --> 13:50.255
But you must find
the proper outlet for your rage.

13:50.362 --> 13:52.728
Fire a weapon
at your television screen...

13:52.832 --> 13:54.959
pick a fight with someone
weaker than you...

13:55.067 --> 13:57.934
or write a threatening letter
to a celebrity.

13:58.037 --> 14:00.597
So when you go out for a drive...

14:00.706 --> 14:05.234
remember to leave your murderous
anger where it belongs- at home.

14:07.313 --> 14:09.008
<i>[ Applause ]</i>

14:09.114 --> 14:12.174
And as if that film wasn't enough,
we have a special guest.

14:12.284 --> 14:16.744
Why, it's Curtis E. Bear,
the courtesy bear.

14:16.856 --> 14:18.756
## [ Hums ]

14:18.858 --> 14:23.056
For the next three hours, this bear will
take your verbal and physical abuse...

14:23.162 --> 14:25.062
with good nature and aplomb.

14:25.164 --> 14:28.600
So, if you'll all just grab one of these
two-by-fours-

14:28.701 --> 14:31.670
Um, Chief, can I at least
shield my crotch?

14:31.770 --> 14:34.261
Bears can't talk, Eddie.

14:34.373 --> 14:36.068
<i>- [ Shouting ]
- [ Eddie Gasps ]</i>

14:36.175 --> 14:39.144
<i>- [ Blows Landing ]
- [ Chattering ]</i>

14:40.613 --> 14:42.877
Well, Simpson,
did you learn something today?

14:42.982 --> 14:45.075
Oh, did I ever.

14:45.184 --> 14:49.177
And that herbal anger rinse
just washed the rage right out of me.

14:49.288 --> 14:53.588
And remember, Midge, you feel
the need to rage, you call me, right?

14:53.692 --> 14:57.423
I won't even get sexual or nothin'-
unless that's what you want.

14:57.529 --> 14:59.759
<i>- [ Door Opens, Closes ]
- But that's not what you want, right?</i>

14:59.865 --> 15:01.765
No, thanks.

15:01.867 --> 15:03.698
But thanks.

15:03.802 --> 15:07.067
[ Chattering ]

15:07.172 --> 15:09.538
After you, sweetheart.

15:09.642 --> 15:11.610
Oh, no. You first, ma'am.

15:11.710 --> 15:13.701
Well, somebody go first.

15:13.812 --> 15:16.906
- Well, not me.
- I'm not goin' until she goes.

15:17.016 --> 15:18.916
Oh, for crying out loud!

15:19.018 --> 15:23.045
Oh. Oh. Okay.
Calm down.Just think.

15:23.155 --> 15:25.316
What would Curtis E. Bear do?

15:25.424 --> 15:29.383
- [ Honking ]
- Move it! I gotta return this suit!

15:29.495 --> 15:31.656
<i>[ Tires Screeching ]</i>

15:31.764 --> 15:33.459
Hmm.

15:34.733 --> 15:37.668
Get out of the way!

15:37.770 --> 15:40.739
<i>-[ Tires Screeching ]
- Oh, no! No!</i>

15:40.839 --> 15:42.739
[ Horn Honking ]

15:42.841 --> 15:45.901
[ Screams ]

15:46.011 --> 15:47.740
- Ya!
- [ Alarm Wailing ]

15:47.846 --> 15:49.746
We're free! We're free!

15:50.849 --> 15:53.511
Whoa! Thanks, chick-dude.

15:53.619 --> 15:55.519
Well, I hope you're happy, Simpson.

15:55.621 --> 15:59.057
Those prisoners were one day away
from being completely rehabilitated.

15:59.158 --> 16:02.218
I'm tearing up your license.

16:03.629 --> 16:06.530
Ah, geez. Darned laminated-

16:06.632 --> 16:09.192
Would you mind? I got stubby fingers.
[ Chuckles ]

16:09.301 --> 16:12.202
[ Groans ]

16:14.540 --> 16:17.839
[ Groans ]
How could they take away my license?

16:17.943 --> 16:21.310
- It feels like I lost a limb.
- Well, that's a turnoff.

16:21.413 --> 16:24.041
Hey, why don't you come
to the wild animal park with us?

16:24.149 --> 16:26.674
No. Your father drives
like an old lady.

16:26.785 --> 16:28.685
At least I've got a license.

16:28.787 --> 16:31.915
- [ Groans ]
- Come on, kids. I went too far.

16:33.826 --> 16:35.726
<i>- [ Door Slams ]
- [ Sighs ]</i>

16:35.828 --> 16:38.820
<i>[ Elephant Trumpets ]</i>

16:38.931 --> 16:41.161
<i>- [ Growling ]
- [ Trumpeting Continues ]</i>

16:41.266 --> 16:44.064
Ah, what a gyp.
They're all just lyin' around.

16:44.169 --> 16:45.727
Do something!

16:45.838 --> 16:48.272
Bart, they're not here
to entertain us.

16:48.374 --> 16:51.571
I've seen plays
that were more exciting than this.

16:51.677 --> 16:53.907
Honest to God. Plays!

16:54.013 --> 16:55.640
<i>[ Animal Calling ]</i>

16:55.748 --> 16:58.911
I don't wanna pay four bucks to watch
some monkey wannabe laying in the sun!

16:59.018 --> 17:01.145
But, Dad, lemurs are nocturnal.

17:01.253 --> 17:04.188
Don't worry, honey.
Daddy will fix that broken animal.

17:04.289 --> 17:07.554
- No!
- I'm not gonna hurt him.
I'm just gonna wake him up.

17:07.659 --> 17:10.287
[ Shrieking ]

17:10.996 --> 17:12.623
[ Shrieks ]

17:12.731 --> 17:14.925
[ Roars ]

17:15.034 --> 17:17.194
- [ Snarling ]
- [ All Growl ]

17:17.301 --> 17:19.770
[ All Snarling, Grunting ]

17:22.374 --> 17:24.773
Uh-oh. Here's a slingshot, Lisa.

17:26.779 --> 17:29.714
[ Australian Accent ] I told 'em
a chain link fence wouldn't hold rhinos.

17:29.815 --> 17:33.512
Oh, wait. No, I didn't.
I meant to tell 'em.

17:42.194 --> 17:44.219
[ Shrieks, Muffled Grunting ]

17:44.329 --> 17:48.390
[ Muffled Laughing ]

17:48.500 --> 17:52.834
[ Screaming ]

17:52.938 --> 17:54.530
- [ Screaming ]
- [ Snarling ]

17:55.674 --> 17:58.142
Don't worry, kids.
I know just what to do.

17:58.243 --> 18:00.643
-Jumanji!
- [ All Snarling ]

18:02.114 --> 18:04.412
Does anything from the movies
actually work?

18:04.516 --> 18:07.246
[ Both Whimpering ]

18:08.387 --> 18:10.378
- [ Both Grunt ]
- Ah, nuts!

18:10.489 --> 18:13.219
Isn't there anybody who can
round up these thunder lizards?

18:13.325 --> 18:15.691
Uh, they'd need
a pretty rugged vehicle.

18:15.794 --> 18:18.763
- And a heart to match.
- Hmm.

18:18.864 --> 18:22.061
I'd like to help you, Chief,
but my license was revoked.

18:22.167 --> 18:24.658
Seems I'm full of rage.

18:24.770 --> 18:28.171
Then do it for this adorable
little puppy.

18:28.273 --> 18:30.173
Look at the puppy, Marge.

18:30.275 --> 18:33.711
- That's your hat.
- She's good, Chief.

18:33.812 --> 18:36.975
Now if you'll excuse me,
I've got some dust that needs busting.

18:38.117 --> 18:40.051
- [ People Screaming ]
- This is Kent Brockman...

18:40.152 --> 18:43.053
at the scene of
a level three rhino alert.

18:43.155 --> 18:46.215
- [ Screaming ]
- Authorities say there's no
immediate danger to anyone-

18:46.325 --> 18:49.055
except those three luckless people
whom we'll identify...

18:49.161 --> 18:51.789
<i>once the rhinos
spit out their wallets.</i>

18:51.897 --> 18:54.627
- [ Gasps ]
- Back! Back, I say!

18:54.733 --> 18:57.258
[ Snarling ]

18:57.369 --> 18:59.303
Oh, no! I'm out of popcorn!

18:59.404 --> 19:02.168
<i>- Throw your peanuts!
- You throw your peanuts!</i>

19:02.274 --> 19:04.208
[ All Screaming ]

19:04.309 --> 19:06.436
- [ Tires Screeching ]
- [ Horn Honking ]

19:06.545 --> 19:09.537
- [ Bart ] Look! It's Mom!
- Out of the way!

19:09.648 --> 19:12.242
- [ Honks ]
- Move it or lose it! Get going, you!

19:12.351 --> 19:14.911
[ Horn Honking ]

19:17.089 --> 19:19.057
This ought to hold 'em.

19:19.158 --> 19:23.561
There's one missing, mate. If we don't find him,
it'll be my ass on the barbie!

19:23.662 --> 19:26.130
- [ Snarling ]
- [ All Whimpering ]

19:26.231 --> 19:28.722
<i>[ Horn Honking ]</i>

19:28.834 --> 19:32.235
- Get in! Get in!
- [ Both Grunt ]

19:32.337 --> 19:35.204
- Come on, Homer!Jump!
- [ Grunts ]

19:35.307 --> 19:39.676
Oh! When will Detroit build a sunroof
for the husky gentleman?

19:39.778 --> 19:41.336
- [ Shrieks ]
- [ Snarling ]

19:41.446 --> 19:44.074
[ Screaming, Whimpering ]

19:44.183 --> 19:48.210
[ Screaming ]
Ah, no!

19:48.320 --> 19:50.345
[ People Gasping ]

19:50.455 --> 19:52.548
[ Whimpering, Sobbing ]

19:52.658 --> 19:54.558
Hey, anybody seen Homer today?

19:54.660 --> 19:56.525
- Here. [ Babbling ]
- There he goes.

19:56.628 --> 19:58.994
[ Screaming ]
Ow!

19:59.097 --> 20:02.533
- It's not my rhino!
- [ All Gasp ]

20:02.634 --> 20:05.000
[ Screaming ]

20:05.103 --> 20:07.833
[ Screams ]

20:07.940 --> 20:10.568
Oh, thank you, God.

20:10.676 --> 20:13.804
<i>And thank you, Port-a-John.
You really saved my-</i>

20:13.912 --> 20:16.506
[ Screams ]
Who's out there?

20:18.283 --> 20:21.081
[ Shrieks ]
Oh, I'm gonna die!

20:21.186 --> 20:23.654
Jesus, Allah, Buddha,
I love you all!

20:25.090 --> 20:27.752
<i>- [ Groans ]
- [ Homer ] Nice rhino.</i>

20:34.266 --> 20:37.827
[ Gasps ]
Oh, no! She's not gonna make it.

20:37.936 --> 20:40.871
Hmm. Looks like it's time
for plan ''B.''

20:40.973 --> 20:43.339
<i>One, two...</i>

20:43.442 --> 20:45.467
three, ''B''!

20:45.577 --> 20:47.044
[ Grunts ]

20:50.215 --> 20:53.582
[ Shrieks, Snarling ]

20:53.685 --> 20:57.280
It's okay, Homie.
You can come out now.

20:57.389 --> 20:59.687
<i>Uh, give me a minute.</i>

21:00.859 --> 21:05.558
[ Grunting, Yelps ]

21:05.664 --> 21:07.859
Oh, Marge! You saved me!

21:07.966 --> 21:11.561
Wow! You are so much cooler
than Milhouse's mom.

21:11.670 --> 21:13.661
Yeah. Way to channel
that rage, Simpson.

21:13.772 --> 21:15.967
How did you know your plan
would work, Mom?

21:16.074 --> 21:19.407
<i>Thanks for asking.
Well, I was watching Dateline...</i>

21:19.511 --> 21:23.572
and Stone Phillips said S.U.V.'s
always roll over when you turn sharply...

21:23.682 --> 21:26.276
and the gas tanks explode
at the drop of a hat.

21:26.385 --> 21:29.252
And she also knew
if a rhino sees a flame...

21:29.354 --> 21:31.584
he'll instinctively
try to put it out.

21:31.690 --> 21:33.590
Stone Phillips again.

21:33.692 --> 21:35.887
Is there anything
that guy doesn't know?

21:35.994 --> 21:38.690
Why, this Stone Phillips
sounds like quite a bloke.

21:38.797 --> 21:40.958
What television network
is he on?

21:41.066 --> 21:42.966
Why, NBC, of course.

21:43.068 --> 21:47.266
NBC has lots of great shows, and their
news and sports coverage can't be beat.

21:47.372 --> 21:50.000
Do you think there's anything great
on NBC right now?

21:50.108 --> 21:52.042
Oh, I'm sure of it.

21:52.144 --> 21:55.011
But there's only one way
to find out.

21:55.113 --> 21:57.604
<i>[ Homer ] I'd like to read
the following statement...</i>

21:57.716 --> 21:59.445
<i>- but I do so under-
- [ Gun Cocks ]</i>

21:59.551 --> 22:01.109
<i>my own free will.</i>

22:01.219 --> 22:03.983
<i>''It has come to my attention
that NBC sucks.</i>

22:04.089 --> 22:07.286
<i>''I apologize for misleading you and urge you
to watch as many Fox shows as possible.</i>

22:07.392 --> 22:11.988
<i>So, in summary, NBC bad, Fox good. ''
CBS great.</i>

22:12.097 --> 22:14.190
<i>- [ Gunshot ]
- [ Body Hits Ground ]</i>

22:14.299 --> 22:16.392
<i>[ Gunshots Continue ]</i>

22:40.492 --> 22:42.255
<i>- [ Gunshot ]
- [ Body Hits Ground ]</i>

